6. User Roles

## Project Manager

Responsibilities:

- Create project tasks
- Edit project tasks
- Delete project tasks
- Assign tasks
- Monitor task progress
- View all records

## Team Member

Responsibilities:

- View assigned tasks only
- Update task status
- Add work notes
- Complete assigned tasks

Restrictions:

- Cannot create tasks
- Cannot delete tasks
- Cannot modify restricted fields

7. Access Control Implementation

Access Control Lists (ACLs) are configured to ensure secure access to project records.

### Project Manager Permissions

- Create Records
- Read All Records
- Update All Records
- Delete Records

### Team Member Permissions

- Read Assigned Records
- Update Status
- Update Work Notes

8. Workflow Process

The workflow follows these steps:

1. Project Manager creates a project task.
2. Task is assigned to a Team Member.
3. Flow Designer sends a notification.
4. Team Member updates task status.
5. Project Manager monitors progress.
6. Completion notification is generated automatically.

9. Testing

